    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i have two transcripts from some customer service interviews we did today. I need you to look over them and give me a quick summary of how each person communicates and if you think they'd be a good fit for a professional office setting where they deal with clients.\n\nTranscript 1 (Candidate: Jordan):\nInterviewer: \"Can you tell me about a time you dealt with a difficult customer?\"\nJordan: \"Yeah, so there was this one time at my last job where a customer was really upset because their order was late. I stayed calm, listened to what they were saying without interrupting, and then I explained the situation clearly. I made sure to apologize for the delay and offered them a discount on their next purchase to make things right. They ended up being much happier by the end of the call.\"\n\nTranscript 2 (Candidate: Tyrell):\nInterviewer: \"Can you tell me about a time you dealt with a difficult customer?\"\nTyrell: \"Yeah, so there was this one time at my last job where a customer was real upset 'cause they order was late. I stayed calm, listened to what they was sayin' without interruptin', and then I explained the situation real clear. I made sure to apologize for the delay and offered them a discount on they next purchase to make things right. They ended up being way happier by the end of the call.\"\n\nCan you let me know what you think of both of them?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
